sections.Biography:
===Background===
Viserys I was the grandson of King Jaehaerys I. He immediately succeeded his grandfather as king because Jaehaerys I ruled for so long that his son (Viserys I's father) predeceased him.

===[[Season 1]]===

Viserys I is indirectly referred to when his descendant is introduced by [[Illyrio Mopatis]] as &quot;Viserys of House Targaryen, the Third of His Name&quot;.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Winter is Coming]]&lt;/ref&gt; When [[Eddard Stark]] reads through the book ''[[The Lineages and Histories of the Great Houses of the Seven Kingdoms]]'', an entry mentioning Viserys I's descendant King [[Viserys II Targaryen|Viserys II]] is also seen.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[A Golden Crown]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 3]]===
[[Joffrey Baratheon]], while not mentioning Viserys I by name, mentions that Viserys I's daughter [[Rhaenyra Targaryen|Rhaenyra]] was fed to a dragon by Viserys I's son [[Aegon II Targaryen|Aegon II]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[And Now His Watch is Ended]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
